The paper deals with sparse signal recovery, which is a problem in signal processing and machine learning. The use of Bayesian methods and scale mixture priors is also a common approach in information theory and machine learning. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses algorithmic development and empirical results, which could fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
